      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "constructor_resolver_chain_indirection",
      "summary": "Repeated new/default/resolve/withDefaults chains create call-depth and validation churn without meaningful policy separation.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/rectify/rectify.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
        "goseg/main.go",
        "goseg/system/wifi_runtime_api.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`rectify.go` has `newRectifyRuntime` -> `NewRectifyRuntime` -> `NewRectifyRuntimeWithDependencies` -> `withDefaultsRectifyRuntime` -> `resolveRectifyRuntime` -> `resolveRectifyRuntimeWithDefaults` before handlers run.",
        "`operations_runtime.go` re-resolves runtime in multiple helper paths (`resolveWorkflowRuntime`, `resolveWorkflowRuntimeWithDefaults`, `emitWorkflowTransition`, `publishTransition`) even after a runtime is already built.",
        "`main.go` introduces wrapper methods (`bootstrapRuntimeWith`, `resolveBootstrapRuntime`, `withDefaults`, and thin `bootstrap/startServer/runC2cCheck` methods) primarily for callback forwarding and nil checks.",
        "`wifi_runtime_api.go` similarly layers default and override construction (`NewWiFiRuntime`, `NewWiFiRuntimeWith`, service constructor checks) while most methods directly forward into runtime methods."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Collapse each subsystem to one explicit runtime builder plus one validation boundary; pass fully-built runtimes downward and avoid re-resolving in leaf helpers.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
